This article is an executive order issued by President Barack Obama in 2014. The order states that amendments are being made to the Manual for Courts-Martial, United States. These amendments are described in an attached annex. The order specifies that these amendments will take effect immediately, but they will not apply retroactively to any acts that were not punishable at the time they were committed. Additionally, the order clarifies that any ongoing nonjudicial punishment proceedings, investigations, trials, or other actions can continue as if the amendments had not been made.